WEBVTT

00:06.270 --> 00:09.501
ANNOUNCER:
And that's just the beginning.

00:09.540 --> 00:11.508
At Harold Equity,

00:11.540 --> 00:15.772
wefve seen a 31% rise
In biotechnology.

00:15.810 --> 00:20.577
And a 52% rise
in holographic imaging.

00:20.620 --> 00:23.043
Thank you, stock holders,
for helping

00:23.090 --> 00:25.650
Harold Equity
look to the future.

00:25.690 --> 00:27.351
Now let's give a big hand to

00:27.390 --> 00:28.652
the board of directors
of Harold Equity.

00:28.690 --> 00:30.783
ELI:
This isn't about morals.
It's about money.

00:30.830 --> 00:32.752
He'll try to make it
about your backstory.

00:32.800 --> 00:34.222
He needs to go there
because he can't

00:34.260 --> 00:35.522
stand on his record
as a CEO.

00:35.560 --> 00:36.367
The bastard.

00:36.400 --> 00:38.288
But you stay calm.
Keep your voice low.

00:38.330 --> 00:41.163
He gets you to raise your voice,
or lose your cool, he wins.

00:41.200 --> 00:43.668
And if he asks me
about killing my wife?

00:43.710 --> 00:45.803
Well, there's no "if."
He will ask you.

00:45.840 --> 00:48.809
That's his only play...
I was asking my
legalconsukant

00:48.840 --> 00:50.273
Mrs. Florrick?

00:50.310 --> 00:52.778
Say you didn't.
It's the truth, isn't it?

00:52.820 --> 00:55.141
It is.

00:55.180 --> 00:56.010
Thank you.

00:56.050 --> 00:58.143
You're trying
to take back the company

00:58.190 --> 00:59.350
that was stolen from you.

00:59.390 --> 01:01.255
This is about the
30% decline

01:01.290 --> 01:03.781
in stock price since
Gerald Drescher took over.

01:03.830 --> 01:05.422
_ And the vote
IS gonng my way?

01:05.460 --> 01:07.291
We swung Brynford Mutual
your way this morning.

01:07.330 --> 01:09.298
36,000 shares.
Good.

01:09.330 --> 01:10.695
And your firm will have a

01:10.730 --> 01:12.766
five percent stake,
Mrs. Florrick.

01:12.800 --> 01:15.735
That must look good for you,
making so much money.

01:15.770 --> 01:18.807
Yes, it does.
Happy days.

01:18.840 --> 01:23.800
You know, others may find your
cynicism bracing, Mrs. Florrick.

01:23.850 --> 01:25.704
I find it charming.

01:25.750 --> 01:26.739
ANNOUNCER:
Ladies and gentleman,
Colin Sweeny.

01:26.780 --> 01:28.714
Okay, here we go.
First line?

01:28.750 --> 01:32.618
I believe in stem cells.
That is our future.

01:32.660 --> 01:33.410
Good!

01:33.460 --> 01:35.883
(applause, booing)
Boos? Really?

01:35.920 --> 01:38.582
How gauche.

01:40.860 --> 01:41.895
SWEENEY:
Ladies and gentlemen...
He's weird with you.

01:41.930 --> 01:43.591
Yep.

01:43.630 --> 01:46.235
...my company has been
mismanaged.
(cell phone rings)

01:46.270 --> 01:48.534
It has seen seen
its value drop by 30%...

01:48.570 --> 01:49.639
Yeah, what's wrong?

01:49.670 --> 01:51.467
We're being evicted.
We're not being evicted. Here...

01:51.510 --> 01:52.909
That's what he said,
he said 90 days.

01:52.940 --> 01:54.168
Don't dramatize it.

01:54.210 --> 01:56.576
He said it's a condo conversion.
Walt, waIt,
what's going on?

01:56.610 --> 01:58.441
Mr. Pedrono
from the eighth floor,

01:58.480 --> 01:59.640
he's here to inspect
the apartment, and tell us

01:59.680 --> 02:01.568
to get out in 90 days.

02:01.620 --> 02:04.145
This is going on now?

02:04.190 --> 02:05.680
I can talk to her
if she wants.
Do you want to talk to him?

02:05.720 --> 02:07.210
Yeah, put him on.
Alicia, come on.

02:07.260 --> 02:08.409
Mrs. Florrick,

02:08.460 --> 02:10.189
I didn't want you to get
the wrong impression.

02:11.590 --> 02:13.751
Um, what's good news,
Mr. Pedrono?

02:13.800 --> 02:16.519
We're giving all the tenants
a chance to own and not rent.

02:16.570 --> 02:17.889
I told your husband
about it a year ago.

02:17.930 --> 02:19.830
You told Peter?
Oh, yes.

02:19.870 --> 02:21.929
We've had this
in the works for a while.

02:21.970 --> 02:23.403
Your lease is up in 90 days,

02:23.440 --> 02:24.839
and we're giving you
a chance to purchase.

02:24.870 --> 02:26.633
Um, so we're being
threatened with eviction?

02:26.680 --> 02:27.874
No, you're being
given the chance

02:27.910 --> 02:29.207
of first refusal to purchase

02:29.250 --> 02:30.547
as is your right
as a current tenant.

02:30.580 --> 02:32.172
Okay, let's talk

02:32.220 --> 02:33.778
later today, Mr. Pedrono.

02:33.820 --> 02:36.641
But for the moment, please delay
your inspection, okay?

02:36.690 --> 02:37.884
If that's what you'd like.

02:37.920 --> 02:40.559
But please get back to me soon--
we need to know your plans.

02:40.590 --> 02:41.784
You'll be the
first person I'll call.

02:41.820 --> 02:43.720
Multitasking?
Like you wouldn't believe.

02:43.760 --> 02:45.751
So, where are we
on speakers?

02:45.790 --> 02:47.394
Um, Drescher's side has
five at microphones.

02:47.430 --> 02:48.852
Yes, Peter,
when you get this message,

02:48.900 --> 02:50.788
call me back. Thanks.

02:50.830 --> 02:53.230
There is something else,
I just happened

02:53.270 --> 02:56.603
to overhear Drescher's
lawyer on her cell.
ELI: Just happened?

02:56.640 --> 02:58.198
More or less. _
She was celebrating

02:58.240 --> 02:59.901
because they just
moved some late shares

02:59.940 --> 03:00.929
to Drescher's column.

03:02.410 --> 03:03.707
Wishful thinking?
Sounded real.

03:03.750 --> 03:05.604
Sounded like she has
enough to beat Sweeney.

03:05.650 --> 03:07.470
36,800 shares.

03:07.520 --> 03:09.818
Which mutual fund
is in play?

03:09.850 --> 03:11.943
I don't know. I thought
everyone was firmed up.

03:11.990 --> 03:13.810
Caitlin, hi.
Are you in the war room?

03:13.860 --> 03:15.953
Yes.
Is Diane there?

03:15.990 --> 03:17.389
No, he went out
about an hour ago.

03:17.430 --> 03:20.251
Who do we have
with 36,800 shares?

03:20.300 --> 03:21.722
Uh, let me check.
Uh, It's Alicia.

03:21.760 --> 03:24.490
Which of the mutual funds
has 36,800 votes?

03:24.530 --> 03:26.669
(overlapping chatter)
We're checking.

03:26.700 --> 03:27.792
It doesn't sound familiar.

03:27.840 --> 03:28.761
It doesn't, does it?
Is Will there?

03:28.800 --> 03:29.835
Yes, in his office.

03:29.870 --> 03:31.406
Well, this used to be his case,

03:31.440 --> 03:32.771
so see_ if that
number rIngs a bell.

03:32.810 --> 03:34.801
Okay, he's in with somebody.
Well, interrupt him.

03:34.840 --> 03:36.774
We have ten minutes
till the vote.

03:36.810 --> 03:38.471
DEERFIELD:
You're suspended
for six months, Will.

03:38.510 --> 03:40.410
This is serious business.
I'm not sayIng It's not.

03:40.450 --> 03:43.248
But I'm more than a lawyer.
I run a business here.

03:43.290 --> 03:44.848
DEERFIELD:
Which is why the
disciplinary board is

03:44.890 --> 03:46.858
allowing you to be here,
in your office,

03:46.890 --> 03:48.551
but that's all.
Then tell me the rules.

03:48.590 --> 03:50.353
If you want there
to be no crossover,

03:50.390 --> 03:52.494
then tell me what I can't...
CAITLIN: I'm sorry, Mr. Gardner,

03:52.530 --> 03:53.997
Alicia said she needs
an answer rIght now.

03:54.030 --> 03:56.260
What's wrong?
She's at
the proxy fight.

03:56.300 --> 03:57.767
They're worried 36,800 shares

03:57.800 --> 03:59.734
have switched sides and they
don't know which ones.

03:59.770 --> 04:01.465
Okay, here we go, Lionel.

04:01.500 --> 04:04.503
Does my suspension prevent me
from answering that question?

04:04.540 --> 04:06.508
Well, does the question
have to do with

04:06.540 --> 04:07.768
the legal side of Lockhart/
Gardner, or the business side?

04:07.810 --> 04:09.801
Mr. Sweeney is a
client we represent

04:09.850 --> 04:11.044
both criminally
and financially.

04:11.080 --> 04:13.378
But at the moment,
we've been asked

04:13.420 --> 04:14.648
to consult on
his proxy fight.

04:14.680 --> 04:16.511
Legally consult?
And financially.

04:16.550 --> 04:17.414
ALICIA:
Caitlin.

04:17.450 --> 04:18.781
We're nearing a vote.

04:18.820 --> 04:20.788
I know, Mr. Gardner is trying
to figuring out whether
he can answer.

04:20.820 --> 04:22.481
And if Caitlin
rephrases the question

04:22.530 --> 04:23.952
as a business-only question?
Such as?

04:23.990 --> 04:25.457
How many proxy votes,
absent any...

04:25.490 --> 04:27.799
Will, you can't
give her the question.

04:27.830 --> 04:28.819
She has to ask the question.

04:28.860 --> 04:29.758
(sighs)
You're kidding.

04:29.800 --> 04:31.791
To advise a subordinate
on a legal question

04:31.830 --> 04:33.468
is to offer legal advice.

04:33.500 --> 04:36.298
Okay, then we just sit here.

04:36.340 --> 04:38.604
How about Mr. Gold?
WILL: Yes.

04:38.640 --> 04:40.801
Part of our firm is
Mr. Gold's crisis management.

04:40.840 --> 04:43.638
Can _she ask me a
question as to that?

04:45.750 --> 04:47.513
Sure, go ahead.
Take your time.

04:49.750 --> 04:53.356
She can ask questions regarding
the crisis management,

04:53.390 --> 04:56.427
but she has to formulate
the questions.

04:57.860 --> 05:00.397
Hold on.
(clears throat)

05:00.430 --> 05:03.922
Mr._Gold is concerned
his client Will lose

05:03.970 --> 05:08.339
the proxy fight due to
the loss of 36,800 votes.

05:08.370 --> 05:10.634
Do you have any idea
who they might belong to?

05:14.540 --> 05:15.768
Tenley Mutual.

05:15.810 --> 05:19.109
Diane's leaving there now. Try
her cell and you might get her.

05:19.150 --> 05:22.938
No, thank you.
We'll be in touch.
(cell phone rings)

05:22.990 --> 05:24.639
Hello, Caitlin.

05:24.690 --> 05:27.909
Uh, yes, I had to
switch off during the meeting.

05:27.960 --> 05:29.882
No, we're leaving now.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.956
Hold on a minute.

05:39.100 --> 05:41.660
Mr. Tenley.

05:41.700 --> 05:43.099
Did you just lie to me?

05:43.140 --> 05:44.869
SWEENEY:
I'm stronger for it.

05:44.910 --> 05:46.434
I'm tougher for it.

05:46.480 --> 05:49.074
And I'm ready
to retake the reigns

05:49.110 --> 05:50.907
of the company I created.

05:50.950 --> 05:52.941
(applause)

05:52.980 --> 05:54.971
He said he told you
a year ago.

05:55.020 --> 05:57.944
He's lying.
I never met a Mr. Pedrono.

05:57.990 --> 05:59.753
You know what he's doing,
don't you?

05:59.790 --> 06:01.087
Establishing a timeline.
That's right.

06:01.120 --> 06:02.519
He needs to give fair warning

06:02.560 --> 06:03.481
before he can enforce
an eVIction.

06:03.530 --> 06:04.485
Would you sign an affidavit
to that effect?

06:04.530 --> 06:07.658
I will. But you should
think about doing it.

06:07.700 --> 06:09.497
Buying.

06:09.530 --> 06:11.862
Oh, I don't know.

06:11.900 --> 06:12.992
You like it.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.132
The kids like it.

06:14.170 --> 06:15.990
It's a lot of debt to take on.

06:16.040 --> 06:18.133
I thought you were making the
really big bucks over there.

06:18.170 --> 06:21.003
(chuckles)
Yeah, that's me.

06:21.040 --> 06:22.871
Okay, I'll talk to
you later, Peter.

06:24.810 --> 06:26.675
Oh, uh, hey, it's Eli.
We have a problem.

06:26.720 --> 06:28.039
PETER:
When don't we have
a problem, Eli?

06:28.080 --> 06:29.911
Were you just on with Alicia?
Was I?

06:29.950 --> 06:30.780
Yeah, why?

06:30.820 --> 06:33.687
You just sounded...

06:33.720 --> 06:35.984
good together. I was
standing right next to her.

06:36.020 --> 06:38.727
Eli, stop scheming.

06:38.760 --> 06:41.729
Know, what's hurting my
chances to being governor today?

06:41.760 --> 06:43.591
A blog called
the "Cook County-ienne."

06:43.630 --> 06:45.666
It says the State's Attorney's
office is a hotbed

06:45.700 --> 06:47.759
of workplace sex,
and that you approve of it.

06:47.800 --> 06:48.869
And when is a blog ever wrong?

06:48.900 --> 06:50.936
Peter, it is specific.
It says that

06:50.970 --> 06:52.870
two ASAs had sex on your office

06:52.910 --> 06:54.571
couch three nights ago.

06:55.980 --> 06:59.575
Eli, we can't listen to every
stupid piece of gossip.

06:59.620 --> 07:00.871
Yes, but we can be responding

07:00.920 --> 07:02.649
to every piece
that involves you and sex.

07:02.690 --> 07:04.908
We are vulnerable
on sex issues, Peter,

07:04.950 --> 07:07.054
for reasons I hope
I don't have to spell out.

07:07.090 --> 07:09.888
You swore you would run
a clean office. This is dirty.

07:09.930 --> 07:11.784
So, we can get him
back on our side?

07:11.830 --> 07:14.094
DIANE:
They'll swing the 36,800 shares
to Sweeney

07:14.130 --> 07:16.121
